comment.body:
I'm not sure if this should be blocked. The popup leads to a discount coupon which may be useful to some user. The current popup is redundant by another banner, but not sure if this is always the case. Add
```
www.dmm.co.jp#$##campaign-popup { display: none !important; }
www.dmm.co.jp#$#body[style^="overflow:"] { overflow: auto !important; }
```
to User rules. We might later change the decision if it has been proven blocking this is safe.
